                                                                <comments>
                            <comment id="22420" author="juergen.hoeller" created="Sat, 24 Feb 2007 12:33:12 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Ben, could you please have a look at this? The line breaks might get modified during the checkout or during the build there...&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Juergen&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="22532" author="nebhale" created="Sat, 3 Mar 2007 00:24:36 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;The problem appears to be two fold.  First, there are some files with \r&apos;s in them and I can fix those up with a simple dos2unix.  But beyond that, there appears to be a significant problem with some ASCII files being labeled as Binary in the CVS repo.  With them labeled this way, they are not eligible for automatic line ending conversion the way ASCII files are.  I&apos;ll do some research and post the results.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="23976" author="nebhale" created="Thu, 24 May 2007 07:50:34 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Romeo, if you&apos;re still watching this, do you remember offhand how you ran into this problem?  Specifically I&apos;m wondering exactly what script caused it and how you executed the script to get the issue.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="23980" author="rgregorie" created="Thu, 24 May 2007 10:19:20 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;In the file samples/jpetstore/db/hsqldb/server.sh the last word is &quot;jpetstore&quot; and includes a \r. This word is part of the option &quot;-database jpetstore&quot;. On a unicode enabled *nix station the /r is a valid char and thus there is no database &quot;jpetstore&lt;br class=&quot;atl-forced-newline&quot; /&gt;r&quot;.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="27049" author="altumano" created="Mon, 22 Oct 2007 20:29:40 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Same story with Spring 2.0.7 on Mac OS X 10.4.10, also lost several hours because of this bug.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;I believe no end-of-lines are needed in those files at all&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="43136" author="juergen.hoeller" created="Wed, 18 Mar 2009 03:49:50 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Since we are not shipping any samples with Spring 3.0 core anymore, I&apos;m closing this SPR issue...&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Juergen&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
